summary: A resourceful and analytically minded electronic engineer with a proactive mentality, and strong enthusiasm for learning and seeking new challenges. Experienced in the field of embedded systems design, electrical hardware design, integrated circuit design and software design. Possess an intuitive understanding of coding languages and computer architecture. In love with the creative aspect of engineering and software design.

projects: [{'title': 'Automated Gardener', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'A semester-7 university half-year project with the premise to create an automated gardener prototype with a budget of just 200 euros. The prototype was supposed to continuously monitor plants, provide them with water and nutrients and report on the condition of the garden to a user. The team consisted of 5 engineering students: 3 mechanical, 1 mechatronic and 1 electrical. My role as an electrical embedded engineer was to implement a system for periodically identifying the growing state of the plant as well its health condition based on the color of its skin. For this implementation I used a raspberry pi and a Sony Playstation 2 camera. I performed a literature research on the video analysis software based on color and shapes and later composed and integrated the software with desired functionality into a raspberry pi. The final product was capable of identifying the ripeness of the plant based on its size and health condition based on its color as expected.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Fedor', 'last_name': 'Zorin', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical & Electronic Engineer'}]}, {'title': 'Digital Design: Digital Audio Systems Project', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': 'This assignment was about working with a system through which audio signals would be sent at a bandwidth of 2MHz. The system was build in FPGA and featured both transmitter and receiver and had one channel for audio stereo signal, and another channel for speech, both encoded through HDB3. Every student was supposed to do a detailed research on every element of the assignment and realize it in HDL Designer.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Fedor', 'last_name': 'Zorin', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical & Electronic Engineer'}]}, {'title': 'EXPO: Pillbox Reminder', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': "This project's aim was about building an electronic pill container-dispenser, with automatic reminder feature. The results would later be documented and presented to the first year students as a second semester project. The tasks of designing each part of the device were split between the members of the group, which would later collaborate in order to make them work all together. My role was to design a functional software application, with direct access to the device, for which i have chosen Python for it's simple syntax and functionality on every major operating system.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Fedor', 'last_name': 'Zorin', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Electrical & Electronic Engineer'}]}, {'title': 'EXPO: Wireless Bedroom Light', 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': "This project's aim was to design and test a lighting system with multiple switches, with a brightness regulator, all connecting to a master switch through a wireless connection. This system was supposed to be able to be easily integrated into a common house lighting circuitry.
